        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Annual Insurance</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">€1,800-2,200</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Basic + deductible</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Monthly Costs as a Freelancer</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Health insurance:</strong> €120-150/month (basic) or €150-250/month (with supplements)</li>
      <li><strong>Accounting:</strong> €100-300/month (optional but recommended)</li>
      <li><strong>Professional liability insurance:</strong> €20-50/month (depending on profession)</li>
      <li><strong>KvK annual fee:</strong> €0 (registration is one-time)</li>
      <li><strong>Banking fees:</strong> €5-15/month (business account)</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6 mb-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Living costs reality:</strong> Amsterdam is expensive—expect €1,500-2,500/month for a studio/1-bedroom apartment. Rotterdam, Utrecht, and The Hague are 20-30% cheaper. Factor housing costs into your freelance rates before committing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The 30% Ruling (Tax Benefit)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Qualifying expats can receive 30% of their salary tax-free for up to 5 years. This significantly reduces your tax burden. However, as a freelancer, qualifying is more complex than for employees.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">You May Qualify If:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ You were recruited from abroad</li>
          <li>✓ You have specific expertise scarce in NL</li>
          <li>✓ You lived 150+ km from Dutch border for 16 of past 24 months</li>
          <li>✓ You earn above the threshold (€46,107 in 2026)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Freelancer Complications:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• Self-employed don't automatically qualify</li>
          <li>• May need to structure as BV (private company)</li>
